Follow the simple steps to run the following codes in your Linux Terminal.

cd Desktop

Step 1> mkdir scripts
Step 2> cd scripts
Step 3> touch test_script
Step 4> vi test_script (press shift + i to open INSERT mode)
Step 5> paste your desired command / shell
Step 6> Save your file - click esc then shift + : then wq then enter.
Step 7> chmod u+x test_script
Step 8> Now run ./test_script


DONT FORGET TO SAVE THE NECESSARY FILES THAT YOU'RE GOING TO USE IN SHELL SCRIPTING RUNTIME.
